02:50.345 --> 02:55.054
That's the Wednesday night waltz, and we do hope that all of you old-timers enjoyed it a whole lot.

02:55.074 --> 02:57.880
Friends, we're going to dedicate this whole program to the women.

02:58.636 --> 03:03.362
All you women out there, sweet things, we're going to dedicate this whole program to you.

03:03.783 --> 03:13.877
Because you know why, friends, one reason why is the women, they play a bigger part in this forest fire prevention business than most folks realize.

03:13.897 --> 03:15.259
Did you ever stop to think of that?

03:15.559 --> 03:17.502
The women really play a big part in it.

03:17.662 --> 03:22.729
In fact, of course, they always speak of the man around the house wearing the pants.

03:22.809 --> 03:24.932
Well, he does wear the pants.

03:24.952 --> 03:27.816
But I'll tell you one thing Mama has a lot to do with.

03:28.117 --> 03:29.238
what's going on.

03:29.258 --> 03:30.539
She sure does.

03:30.559 --> 03:36.865
They realize that they've got a definite responsibility to prevent these forest fires.

03:36.885 --> 03:38.847
Now, a woman knows the value of things.

03:38.867 --> 03:40.208
Did you ever stop to think of that?

03:40.268 --> 03:40.949
I know you have.

03:41.009 --> 03:42.810
You men out there, you won't acknowledge it.

03:42.830 --> 03:44.912
You won't admit it or anything like that.

03:44.952 --> 03:45.533
I won't either.

03:45.553 --> 03:46.294
I'm a married man.

03:46.334 --> 03:47.595
I got a wife and two children.

03:48.756 --> 03:55.062
But, you know, about, I'd say, I'd say three-thirds of the time, she's right.

03:55.082 --> 03:55.542
And, uh,

03:56.011 --> 03:59.075
These women, they realize the value of things.

03:59.095 --> 04:01.878
A forest is more than just a thing of beauty to them.

04:02.519 --> 04:12.470
It's lumber, and it's furniture, and it's pencils and paper for the kids to go to school, and it's kitchen shelves, and it's kitchen tables.

04:13.171 --> 04:16.114
Well, it's a lot of things that they realize that you don't.

04:17.075 --> 04:17.656
Maybe you don't.

04:17.716 --> 04:18.797
You men I'm talking about.

04:18.897 --> 04:20.359
You don't realize it, and they do.

04:21.500 --> 04:22.862
And they know that trees...

04:23.315 --> 04:29.785
like their own children, must be protected and be allowed to grow up strong and healthy and amount to something.

04:30.406 --> 04:33.651
Now, they look to the future more than the men do.

04:33.671 --> 04:37.036
Through their clubs and by themselves, they're doing a wonderful job.

04:37.637 --> 04:43.446
They're behind tree planting, and they're behind these forester boys in preventing fires.

04:43.466 --> 04:47.112
They're behind them 100%.

04:48.593 --> 04:50.155
I'll tell you a story about a fellow.

04:50.416 --> 05:07.139
I wanted to tell you a story about a fellow that was careless with a fire, and he let it get out into some newly planted trees, and it burned it off, and the police got him and got him up there in the court and all, and they didn't know how to find him or just exactly what to do, and his wife stepped up and said, I'll tell you what to do, Judge.

05:07.159 --> 05:11.766
Said, you just find him to replant these trees, replant them.

05:12.303 --> 05:19.374
Well, it was kind of funny that she stepped in and said that, and so the old judge, he kind of snickered under his breath, and he said, well, that's the fine.

05:19.394 --> 05:20.075
So what did she do?

05:20.115 --> 05:22.298
She got out there and helped him replant all these trees.

05:22.819 --> 05:23.480
Ain't that nice?

05:23.540 --> 05:24.802
That is really fine.

