08:12.967 --> 08:21.200
You know, friends, I know of a case happening about a lady that lived out in the edge of the woods.

08:21.220 --> 08:24.265
The reason I say the edge of the woods, their place joined the woods.

08:25.327 --> 08:32.198
And you know how a woman is about getting out in the yard and raking up all the leaves and the trash and stuff and pile it up and burn it.

08:32.879 --> 08:34.642
Well, that's what she was going to do.

08:34.662 --> 08:35.823
She was cleaning yards.

08:35.843 --> 08:39.970
You know, that's nothing to the ladies to clean yards.

08:40.372 --> 08:43.156
because every so often they'd get out and clean yards.

08:43.176 --> 08:45.380
Well, this particular lady was cleaning yards.

08:46.301 --> 08:53.813
She cleaned up all the trash, the leaves and the rubbish and all that sort of stuff, and she took a lot of pains to burn it in the right place.

08:53.833 --> 08:59.862
And she was sure that she wasn't going to leave the fire unprotected or anything like that, so she stayed with it.

09:00.343 --> 09:06.312
She sat right there with it with the rake in her hand, one of these old-timey rakes, you know, that she raked the yards with.

09:07.355 --> 09:09.677
Well, she was staying there watching her fire burn.

09:09.697 --> 09:15.622
She had it going pretty good, and they had quite a young baby in the house, and it was asleep.

09:16.463 --> 09:19.966
About that time, she heard the baby start crying.

09:19.986 --> 09:21.888
So she called to her husband.

09:21.908 --> 09:27.453
Well, he was sitting around inside the house in the shade, lazy rascal, reading the paper.

09:27.473 --> 09:32.738
And he's sitting around there reading, and she called to him and told him to come and watch the fire.

09:32.758 --> 09:33.659
The baby was crying.

09:33.699 --> 09:35.100
She wanted to go inside the house.

09:35.924 --> 09:37.046
He said, all right, honey.

09:37.266 --> 09:38.708
He hollered back, all right, honey.

09:38.788 --> 09:46.098
Well, she figured he'd come on around there and watch the fire, so she went in to see what was happening to the baby.

09:46.118 --> 09:52.527
And so she looked after him, and she'd come back out, come back out expecting to see her husband around there with the rape.

09:52.547 --> 09:54.069
But lo and behold, he wasn't there.

09:54.570 --> 09:56.873
He was still around there buried up in that newspaper.

09:56.913 --> 09:59.637
He'd found something that was awful interesting to him.

10:00.038 --> 10:01.180
And what did she find?

10:01.240 --> 10:02.281
She found the fire.

10:02.682 --> 10:08.991
The sparks had blown out over the fence there into the grass and weeds and had set the woods on fire.

10:09.011 --> 10:10.674
And it was going.

10:10.694 --> 10:12.376
Well, I mean, business picked up then.

10:13.778 --> 10:17.624
And I mean, business really picked up then.

10:17.664 --> 10:19.667
So she hollered to him to come here quick.

10:20.228 --> 10:24.514
And he threw that newspaper down and he come running quick.

10:24.534 --> 10:29.742
So they called in to the forestry boys and they come out on the job and went to work right away.

10:30.025 --> 10:33.470
And it just so happened that they didn't lose but very little acreage.

10:33.810 --> 10:38.616
But that just shows you how little things like that can happen so sudden-like.

10:38.636 --> 10:41.019
Now, she was only gone for just a minute or two there.

10:41.460 --> 10:43.723
And the fire got out in the woods.

10:43.743 --> 10:47.047
